cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing an intent communication system that takes into account the psychology behind what pedestrians are familiar with and what they expect from machines. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with autonomous vehicles and their interaction with pedestrians. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the intent communication system uses mathematical algorithms to integrate pedestrian expectations into the design of physical systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the development and validation of a system for controlling the behavior of autonomous vehicles in the presence of pedestrians. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve computer vision techniques for detecting and tracking pedestrians.
